WEBVTT

00:00.801 --> 00:03.702
<i> [punchy music]</i>

00:04.638 --> 00:07.306
- Milo! Ruby!
Exciting news!

00:07.375 --> 00:09.775
I'm auditioning
for a musical theater troupe.

00:09.844 --> 00:11.143
Or should I say...

00:11.212 --> 00:16.348
♪ Musical theater troooupe ♪

00:17.218 --> 00:18.550
Jazz hands.

00:18.619 --> 00:20.986
- Awesome.
I didn't even know you sang.

00:21.055 --> 00:23.122
- Or that your hands did jazz.

00:23.891 --> 00:25.858
- I've been doing costumes
for this troupe for a while,

00:25.926 --> 00:28.360
but I've finally worked up
the nerve to audition.

00:28.429 --> 00:30.129
- That is exciting, Darby.

00:30.197 --> 00:32.631
We actually have
some exciting news too.

00:32.700 --> 00:35.300
There's a new sandwich shop
opening downtown!

00:35.369 --> 00:37.803
- I feel like my exciting news
was a bit more...

00:37.872 --> 00:38.804
actually exciting?

00:38.873 --> 00:40.139
- It's superhero-themed,

00:40.207 --> 00:41.673
and the grand opening
is Friday.

00:41.742 --> 00:46.378
- "Sumer Sammies: with great
power comes great sandwiches."

00:46.447 --> 00:47.780
- We thought it'd be
a great place to generate buzz

00:47.848 --> 00:49.848
for our graphic novel,
since anyone who's anyone

00:49.917 --> 00:51.650
in the local comic book scene
will be there.

00:51.719 --> 00:53.886
- Not to mention
people who love sandwiches.

00:53.954 --> 00:55.220
This is a rare opportunity

00:55.289 --> 00:58.357
to impress two
hugely influential groups.

00:58.426 --> 01:00.059
- The graphic novel's finished?

01:00.127 --> 01:01.093
both: No.

01:01.162 --> 01:02.561
- But we're doing
a character drop

01:02.630 --> 01:05.297
to give everyone at the opening
a preview of the artwork.

01:05.366 --> 01:07.399
By the way, how are
the drawings going, Ruby?

01:07.468 --> 01:08.967
- Great! I actually have
a few new ones to show you.

01:09.036 --> 01:11.070
Let me grab my sketch pad.

01:11.138 --> 01:14.339
- Aren't you nervous to show
your work to all those people?

01:14.408 --> 01:16.375
- Normally I would be,
but now that I've been working

01:16.444 --> 01:19.278
with Ruby, I feel okay
putting myself out there.

01:19.346 --> 01:22.815
- Really? In front of all
your comic book friends?

01:22.883 --> 01:24.783
All those eyes staring at you,
judging you,

01:24.852 --> 01:26.351
critiquing every single
little thing?

01:26.420 --> 01:28.053
- Well, I wasn't nervous.

01:28.122 --> 01:31.256
[drone whirring]

01:33.561 --> 01:35.727
[whirring intensifies]

01:35.796 --> 01:37.329
[drone beeps]

01:37.398 --> 01:40.299
- Hey-o, have you seen
my pizza drone?

01:40.367 --> 01:41.433
- You mean that one?

01:41.502 --> 01:43.802
[drone beeping]

01:43.871 --> 01:45.871
- Different pizza drone.

01:45.940 --> 01:47.506
Okay, yeah, that one.

01:47.575 --> 01:49.775
I'm using it to make deliveries
so I don't have to.

01:49.844 --> 01:51.944
- Hurley, that's the worst idea
ever.

01:52.012 --> 01:54.746
- Okay, first of all, rude.

01:54.815 --> 01:56.381
And second of all,
that's not the way

01:56.450 --> 01:58.250
you tell someone
you don't like something.

01:58.319 --> 01:59.918
- Yeah, if I'm being
brutally honest,

01:59.987 --> 02:02.187
you do have a tendency
to be too brutally honest.

02:02.256 --> 02:04.389
- What? Like when?

02:04.458 --> 02:05.858
- Uh, like when I got my bangs

02:05.926 --> 02:07.893
and you said it looked like
I cut my hair with an ax.

02:07.962 --> 02:09.761
- Or the time you said
that when I dance,

02:09.830 --> 02:11.463
I look like noodles.

02:11.532 --> 02:14.466
Does this look like noodles
to you?

02:14.535 --> 02:16.935
- Absolutely.
- It's a choice.

02:17.004 --> 02:18.770
- I respectfully disagree.

02:18.839 --> 02:20.572
And you need to adjust
your approach.

02:20.641 --> 02:22.741
Ever heard
of a compliment sandwich?

02:22.810 --> 02:24.543
- What's a compliment sandwich?

02:24.612 --> 02:26.645
- Allow me to explain.

02:26.714 --> 02:28.447
The best way to give
negative feedback

02:28.516 --> 02:30.582
is to hide it
between two compliments,

02:30.651 --> 02:33.919
much like this salami is hiding
between these two slices

02:33.988 --> 02:35.654
of ciabatta.

02:35.723 --> 02:37.990
- You carry a sandwich
in your pocket?

02:38.058 --> 02:39.625
- You don't?

02:39.693 --> 02:41.960
- Okay, here are
the new drawings.

02:42.029 --> 02:44.163
- Oh, great.

02:44.231 --> 02:46.331
Oh, I love this.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.734
Perfect, as always. Ah.

02:48.802 --> 02:51.170
Where's Blorphy?
- Which character is Blorphy?

02:51.238 --> 02:53.772
- Oh, I wrote him as this sort
of lovable, scene-stealing,

02:53.841 --> 02:55.040
super-cute creature.

02:55.109 --> 02:57.309
- I know the type.

02:57.378 --> 02:58.644
- He's gonna be
our breakout star,

02:58.712 --> 03:00.679
especially if Ruby's designs
capture the magic

03:00.748 --> 03:03.282
as they always--

03:03.350 --> 03:04.917
Oh.

03:04.985 --> 03:07.653
Is this, uh--is this him?

03:07.721 --> 03:09.755
- It's just a first draft.

03:09.823 --> 03:12.191
- I gotta say, Ruby...
- [clears throat pointedly]

03:12.259 --> 03:14.059
[mouthing word]

03:14.128 --> 03:18.430
- You're...really on a roll
with these drawings recently.

03:18.499 --> 03:21.166
Lettuce talk about
how great they are.

03:21.235 --> 03:23.902
I'd really be in a pickle
if it wasn't for

03:23.971 --> 03:27.139
this amazing artwork, but--
- Ooh, wow! Really?

03:27.208 --> 03:28.273
That's great.

03:28.342 --> 03:29.841
I was nervous to show you,

03:29.910 --> 03:32.344
but the fact that you love
all of these makes me confident

03:32.413 --> 03:34.112
we're on the right track.
- Well, I--

03:34.181 --> 03:36.081
- Gotta go,
not because all the nice things

03:36.150 --> 03:38.650
you said are making me cry
but because I want to make sure

03:38.719 --> 03:41.687
these are perfect for our
character drop Friday.

03:41.755 --> 03:42.955
Whoo.

03:45.426 --> 03:47.593
- No! What did I do?

03:47.661 --> 03:49.928
I really didn't like
Ruby's Blorphy,

03:49.997 --> 03:52.731
but now she thinks I loved it.
[sighs]

03:52.800 --> 03:54.333
Thanks for the horrible advice,
Hurley.

03:54.401 --> 03:55.567
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:55.636 --> 03:56.635
You can't just tell someone

03:56.704 --> 03:58.270
their advice is horrible
like that.

03:58.339 --> 04:02.407
You gotta sandwich it
between the different layers--

04:02.476 --> 04:04.476
Rude!

04:08.215 --> 04:11.083
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

04:11.151 --> 04:17.055
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

04:17.124 --> 04:18.523
<i> - ♪ "Warped!" ♪</i>
- Check it out, Milo.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.460
I am loving this pizza drone
so much,

04:21.528 --> 04:23.295
I thought I'd use it
in here too.

04:23.364 --> 04:26.331
- It's impressive how much work
you put into being lazy.

04:26.400 --> 04:29.501
- Thanks, it's a gift.
Order up!

04:29.570 --> 04:32.237
[drone whirring]

04:32.306 --> 04:34.172
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

04:34.241 --> 04:36.608
- Look to the sky, people.

04:36.677 --> 04:39.244
[drone beeps]
Oh!

04:39.313 --> 04:40.812
Sorry! I'll send
another slice your way

04:40.881 --> 04:42.447
on the next available flight.

04:45.352 --> 04:46.551
- Hey, Darby.
How'd your audition

04:46.620 --> 04:48.487
for the musical theater troupe
go?

04:48.555 --> 04:51.623
- Oh, it went good,
like I knew it would.

04:51.692 --> 04:54.426
- Great.
Glad you conquered your nerves.

04:54.495 --> 04:55.861
Now it's my turn.
I'm gonna tell Ruby

04:55.929 --> 04:57.763
that I don't like
the Blorphy design.

04:57.831 --> 04:59.064
He's a really important
character.

04:59.133 --> 05:02.200
If we do it right,
he could be our Baby Yoda.

05:02.269 --> 05:05.404
both: Aww, I love Baby Yoda.

05:05.472 --> 05:07.639
- Exactly.
Everyone loves Baby Yoda.

05:07.708 --> 05:10.509
But Ruby's drawing of Blorphy
just looks like...well,

05:10.577 --> 05:12.978
he looks like ham.

05:13.047 --> 05:14.946
- Huh. Well, at least
he looks tasty?

05:15.015 --> 05:17.416
- That's not the point.
He can't be ham.

05:17.484 --> 05:19.418
- What do you have against ham?

05:19.486 --> 05:20.585
- I don't have anything
against ham.

05:20.654 --> 05:22.487
I enjoy ham,
but I don't want to read

05:22.556 --> 05:23.889
a graphic novel about a ham.

05:23.957 --> 05:25.824
I don't wanna buy
ham action figures

05:25.893 --> 05:28.093
or snuggle up to a stuffed ham
when I go to bed.

05:28.162 --> 05:30.462
- Not cool.
I sleep with a stuffed ham,

05:30.531 --> 05:32.698
and you know it.

05:32.766 --> 05:34.633
- I don't have anything
against ham.

05:34.702 --> 05:36.268
It's just wrong
for the character.

05:36.337 --> 05:38.103
And if the comic book fans
at the Super Sammies opening

05:38.172 --> 05:40.205
don't like the design,
our graphic novel

05:40.274 --> 05:43.709
could be canceled before
we even finish making it.

05:43.777 --> 05:45.344
I've gotta tell Ruby
how I really feel.

05:45.412 --> 05:47.145
- Good luck with that.

05:47.214 --> 05:48.980
Who wants crushed red pepper?

05:49.049 --> 05:52.217
[drone whirring]

05:54.254 --> 05:57.522
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

05:57.591 --> 06:00.726
- Hey, Ruby,
do you, uh, have a minute?

06:00.794 --> 06:03.095
I, uh--I need to be honest
about something.

06:03.163 --> 06:04.296
But not brutally honest.

06:04.365 --> 06:07.566
Just the perfectly appropriate
amount of honest.

06:09.169 --> 06:12.204
Blorphy...looks like ham.

06:12.272 --> 06:15.006
I don't think it works
for the character.

06:15.075 --> 06:17.109
Is that--is that okay?

06:18.645 --> 06:20.312
- Sorry, were you talking
to me?

06:20.381 --> 06:22.180
I'm on hold with the dentist.

06:22.249 --> 06:24.116
- Oh, well, do you have
a toothache or something?

06:24.184 --> 06:25.984
- No, I just like the music
dentists play

06:26.053 --> 06:28.353
when they put you on hold,
so sometimes I call Dr. Abrams

06:28.422 --> 06:29.588
just to jam out.

06:29.656 --> 06:31.390
Anyway, what's up?

06:31.458 --> 06:33.859
- Uh, nothing big.

06:33.927 --> 06:36.094
Just wanted to chat
about Blorphy.

06:36.163 --> 06:38.930
- I am so excited you like him
as much as you do.

06:38.999 --> 06:41.933
I really respect your opinion,
and I'd be crushed

06:42.002 --> 06:43.535
if I thought I was
letting you down.

06:43.604 --> 06:45.704
- Oh, my opinion's
not that great.

06:45.773 --> 06:48.840
- No, it really is.
In fact, your encouragement

06:48.909 --> 06:51.543
inspired me to design a whole
bunch of other characters

06:51.612 --> 06:52.778
to look like Blorphy.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.846
- Oh, wow! There's more.

06:54.915 --> 06:58.583
- Blorphy's mom and dad,
brothers and sisters,

06:58.652 --> 07:02.120
aunts, uncles, cousins.

07:02.189 --> 07:04.055
- Well, I definitely see
the resemblance in the, uh...

07:04.124 --> 07:05.891
head region.
- And then I went ahead

07:05.959 --> 07:07.592
and made some life-size
cutouts.

07:09.963 --> 07:11.530
- Gah!

07:11.598 --> 07:12.864
- Too much?

07:12.933 --> 07:15.567
- No! That was a good "Gah!"

07:15.636 --> 07:18.837
Like, "Gah, this is just
so wonderful!"

07:18.906 --> 07:21.440
- Great, because we gotta nail
this character drop.

07:21.508 --> 07:24.242
We're not just introducing
the world to Blorphy.

07:24.311 --> 07:26.745
We're introducing them
to Ruby and Milo.

07:26.814 --> 07:30.115
We only get one shot
at a first impression.

07:30.184 --> 07:31.950
- That's ham--him!

07:33.420 --> 07:36.121
- So let's give people
something they can't ignore.

07:36.190 --> 07:39.991
- Yeah, this is all
very impossible to ignore.

07:41.795 --> 07:46.031
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

07:47.317 --> 07:49.050
<i> [punchy music]</i>

07:49.119 --> 07:51.219
- Sorry, folks.
The pizza drone is out

07:51.288 --> 07:53.955
on a delivery and will be back
shortly to handle your orders.

07:54.024 --> 07:56.057
[people groan and sigh]

07:56.126 --> 07:59.060
- Hurley, the food's
right there.

07:59.129 --> 08:02.197
- Yeah, and I'm all the way
over here.

08:04.568 --> 08:06.067
- Oh, how'd it go, Milo?

08:06.136 --> 08:08.136
Did you and Ruby settle
on a new design for Blorphy?

08:08.205 --> 08:09.738
- Does this answer
your question?

08:09.806 --> 08:10.839
both: Gah!

08:10.908 --> 08:13.642
- That is exactly what I said.

08:13.710 --> 08:15.911
Which is why I came up
with a new plan.

08:15.979 --> 08:17.379
I hired your theater troupe

08:17.447 --> 08:19.881
to act as "random comic book
fans" to give us some

08:19.950 --> 08:22.517
"fake honest feedback"
about Blorphy.

08:22.586 --> 08:25.387
- Oh!
They're coming here?

08:25.455 --> 08:27.355
- Oh, by the way, when I asked
about how your audition went,

08:27.424 --> 08:28.523
they said you never showed up.

08:28.592 --> 08:31.193
- Um, about that...

08:31.261 --> 08:33.261
I chickened out.

08:33.330 --> 08:35.664
I just get so nervous when
I'm in front of lots of people.

08:35.732 --> 08:37.599
Everything goes blurry
and I freeze.

08:37.668 --> 08:40.468
- That's what happens to me
when I drink slushies too fast.

08:40.537 --> 08:42.671
- Plus, my parents didn't
want me taking on another

08:42.739 --> 08:44.306
"nonacademic hobby."

08:44.374 --> 08:46.575
They're always trashin'
my fashion passion.

08:46.643 --> 08:49.010
I'd hate for them
to ding my sing thing.

08:50.480 --> 08:52.814
Sorry, sometimes I rhyme
when I'm flustered.

08:52.883 --> 08:55.417
Mustard!
See? I can't stop.

08:55.485 --> 08:58.019
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

08:58.088 --> 09:00.055
- Okay, everyone.
Ruby's on her way.

09:00.123 --> 09:02.857
Remember, you're acting
as comic book fans.

09:02.926 --> 09:04.993
We'll ask questions,
you'll give opinions,

09:05.062 --> 09:07.395
and the most important thing
is that when we ask

09:07.464 --> 09:09.731
about Blorphy,

09:09.800 --> 09:12.534
you let us know that you don't
like the drawing.

09:12.603 --> 09:15.537
You think it looks like a ham
and it needs to change.

09:15.606 --> 09:16.771
Got it?
- Got it.

09:16.840 --> 09:18.173
When do we get our costumes?

09:18.242 --> 09:20.175
- What? There are no costumes.

09:20.244 --> 09:22.911
- What about accents?
I can do a decent New Yorker.

09:22.980 --> 09:24.312
Should I work it
into the performance?

09:24.381 --> 09:25.480
- You should not.

09:25.549 --> 09:28.116
- [with New York accent]
Hey, I'm walkin' here.

09:28.185 --> 09:30.418
- Hi, Evangeline Hart, 5'4".

09:30.487 --> 09:32.687
Can we sing our feedback?

09:32.756 --> 09:38.059
[vocalizing]

09:38.128 --> 09:40.729
- Or rap, like in "Hamilton"?

09:40.797 --> 09:42.564
♪ His name is Blorphy ♪

09:42.633 --> 09:44.499
♪ Is he even worthy? ♪

09:44.568 --> 09:46.701
- No! No singing, no rapping.

09:46.770 --> 09:48.236
This isn't a performance.

09:48.305 --> 09:49.904
We just need you
to give us feedback

09:49.973 --> 09:51.373
that you don't like Blorphy.

09:51.441 --> 09:52.374
Got it?

09:52.442 --> 09:54.309
<i> - Capisce.</i>
- ♪ Got it ♪

09:54.378 --> 09:56.378
- Milo?
- Ooh, uh, Ruby's coming!

09:56.446 --> 09:58.146
Places, everybody!

09:59.049 --> 10:00.515
- Hello.
- Hey, Ruby.

10:00.584 --> 10:02.917
Everything's ready to go
for our feedback session.

10:02.986 --> 10:04.486
- Thanks for coming.

10:04.554 --> 10:06.121
Our story follows two teenagers

10:06.189 --> 10:08.056
who discover an adorable
space creature

10:08.125 --> 10:09.958
and develop superpowers
that only work

10:10.027 --> 10:11.126
when they're together.

10:11.194 --> 10:12.994
- Great idea. Love the premise.

10:13.063 --> 10:14.629
- I'd read something like that.

10:14.698 --> 10:15.897
- [with New York accent]
Me too.

10:15.966 --> 10:18.600
I'm a New Yorker,
and I love graphic novels.

10:18.669 --> 10:20.035
- Wonderful.

10:20.103 --> 10:22.604
- Hi, Evangeline Hart, 5'4".

10:22.673 --> 10:25.340
I also like the idea.

10:25.409 --> 10:31.946
♪ And it makes me
wanna siiiiiiing ♪

10:32.015 --> 10:34.349
- Wow! Awesome feedback,
everyone.

10:34.418 --> 10:39.387
So...
♪ Positiiiiiiive ♪

10:39.456 --> 10:41.656
- Yes, a great start,
but as we move on,

10:41.725 --> 10:43.858
don't be afraid to give us
negative feedback too.

10:43.927 --> 10:46.094
If you see something
that you don't like,

10:46.163 --> 10:48.463
feel free to say it.
- I don't like your hair.

10:48.532 --> 10:49.931
- Or your shirt.

10:50.867 --> 10:52.967
- I meant feedback
about the novel.

10:53.036 --> 10:55.770
Our goal is to get feedback
on our characters.

10:55.839 --> 10:58.239
What do we think
of the character Blorphy?

10:58.308 --> 11:00.308
- Now, this is really
important because we're doing

11:00.377 --> 11:03.044
a character drop tomorrow,
so he needs to be perfect.

11:03.113 --> 11:08.416
- ♪ What is
a character drop? ♪

11:08.485 --> 11:10.018
- A preview of our characters
to generate buzz

11:10.087 --> 11:11.386
for our graphic novel.

11:11.455 --> 11:12.620
- Like, you're gonna drop
Blorphy from the sky?

11:12.689 --> 11:14.289
Only in New York.

11:14.358 --> 11:16.257
- First, we're not in New York.

11:16.326 --> 11:18.827
And we're gonna hand out flyers
with drawings of Blorphy

11:18.895 --> 11:20.228
and the hashtag
NextGreatHero.

11:20.297 --> 11:23.164
- Boring!

11:23.233 --> 11:24.866
- [with New York accent]
Yeah, you gotta go big,

11:24.935 --> 11:28.470
like a skywriter or fireworks!

11:28.538 --> 11:30.305
- I do like the idea
of a big stunt.

11:30.374 --> 11:32.240
- We're here to talk
about Blorphy's look.

11:32.309 --> 11:35.377
Do you like his look, or does
he remind you of something?

11:35.445 --> 11:37.912
- I got it!
You should drop the flyers

11:37.981 --> 11:40.215
down onto the crowd from above!

11:40.283 --> 11:41.616
- Oh!
- Ooh, that's good.

11:41.685 --> 11:42.917
- While we're at it,
why don't we have them dropped

11:42.986 --> 11:45.053
by a life-sized flying Blorphy?

11:45.122 --> 11:46.955
- I love that.
Great idea, Milo..

11:47.023 --> 11:48.156
- Um, sure, it's a great idea,

11:48.225 --> 11:49.758
but it's impossible
to pull off.

11:49.826 --> 11:51.292
How would we even
get up that high?

11:51.361 --> 11:53.628
- My uncle works
for the power company.

11:53.697 --> 11:56.264
He can loan you
a construction lift.

11:56.333 --> 11:58.266
- Okay, but even if
we got up there,

11:58.335 --> 12:00.101
there's no way to make Blorphy
fly across the sky.

12:00.170 --> 12:03.171
- Ooh, my other uncle owns
a zip line course.

12:03.240 --> 12:05.707
He could string something up,
no prob.

12:05.776 --> 12:08.243
- But we don't even have
a giant stuffed Blorphy.

12:08.311 --> 12:10.745
- My mom sells high school
mascot costumes.

12:10.814 --> 12:12.580
She'd be happy to help!

12:13.650 --> 12:15.216
both: Unbelievable.

12:15.285 --> 12:16.518
- This is incredible, Milo.

12:16.586 --> 12:18.553
Asking for feedback
was a great idea.

12:18.622 --> 12:21.289
- Everything I hoped for.

12:21.358 --> 12:23.525
Do you seriously want to do
this crazy Blorphy stunt?

12:23.593 --> 12:25.026
- Why not?
You're the one who said

12:25.095 --> 12:27.162
if we heard a good idea,
we should take it.

12:27.230 --> 12:29.130
- I did say that, didn't I?

12:29.199 --> 12:31.065
- Hey, Uncle Randall,
can some people I just met

12:31.134 --> 12:32.434
use a lift tomorrow night?

12:33.236 --> 12:35.170
Yeah, the shorter one's fine.

12:35.238 --> 12:37.205
[all cheering]

12:37.274 --> 12:41.743
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

12:41.812 --> 12:44.779
[lift humming]

12:47.884 --> 12:50.652
- This is the shorter one?

12:50.720 --> 12:52.187
Wow, we are high up.

12:52.255 --> 12:54.055
- I can barely even make out
all the people

12:54.124 --> 12:55.323
at the grand opening
down there.

12:55.392 --> 12:57.692
They look like ants.
- Yep, just a bunch

12:57.761 --> 13:01.362
of hugely influential,
uber-critical ants.

13:01.431 --> 13:03.198
- Okay.

13:03.266 --> 13:05.099
Come on, Blorphy.

13:07.604 --> 13:09.771
All right.
Should we let 'er rip?

13:11.875 --> 13:13.741
- Oh, no! Oh, Ruby!

13:13.810 --> 13:16.644
Darn,
I forgot to bring the flyers.

13:16.713 --> 13:17.912
You know, I was really
looking forward

13:17.981 --> 13:19.681
to sharing Blorphy with people.

13:19.749 --> 13:22.083
Oh, well. Let's head back.

13:22.152 --> 13:25.119
- Don't fret, my guy.
I got backups.

13:25.188 --> 13:27.889
I printed a thousand more
of these bad boys

13:27.958 --> 13:29.390
just in case.

13:29.459 --> 13:31.226
- You've thought of everything.

13:32.462 --> 13:35.196
- Now it's time for the world
to meet Blorphy.

13:35.265 --> 13:36.598
On the count of three.

13:36.666 --> 13:39.000
One, two--
- No, Ruby, don't!

13:39.069 --> 13:40.735
[keys jingling]

13:40.804 --> 13:43.404
The key!

13:43.473 --> 13:45.406
- We need that to get down,
right?

13:45.926 --> 13:47.525
- - Oh.!

13:47.594 --> 13:48.760
The key!

13:48.828 --> 13:52.263
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:53.433 --> 13:56.834
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

13:56.903 --> 13:59.804
[indistinct chatter]

14:00.974 --> 14:02.574
- Can anybody hear us?
- We're stuck up here!

14:02.642 --> 14:04.709
- [sighs]
Don't panic. Don't panic.

14:04.778 --> 14:06.945
- I'm not.
- I was talking to me.

14:07.013 --> 14:08.313
- Oh.

14:08.381 --> 14:10.281
- I'm gonna call Hurley
for help.

14:11.785 --> 14:14.619
[phone rings]

14:14.688 --> 14:17.222
- Go for Hurley.
<i> - Hurley! You have to help us!</i>

14:17.290 --> 14:20.158
Look up! We're trapped
on the aerial lift!

14:20.227 --> 14:23.561
- Wow! That's high. Spooky.

14:23.630 --> 14:25.496
Well, hurry down.
They're handing out sandwiches,

14:25.565 --> 14:27.865
and the Guardians of the
Grilled Cheese looks amazing.

14:27.934 --> 14:30.235
- Hurley, you're not listening!
We're stuck up here!

14:30.303 --> 14:32.537
We need you to find the key
and fly it up on your drone.

14:32.606 --> 14:34.372
<i> Please hurry!</i>
- I'm on it.

14:35.942 --> 14:37.642
- My friend Margo
from back home once got stuck

14:37.711 --> 14:40.111
on an elevator for four days.

14:40.180 --> 14:41.579
- The elevator was broken
for four days?

14:41.648 --> 14:43.548
- No, the elevator worked fine.

14:43.617 --> 14:44.582
She accidentally glued
her tongue

14:44.651 --> 14:45.950
to the third-floor button.

14:46.019 --> 14:47.986
The weird part is,
she didn't even want to go

14:48.054 --> 14:49.721
to the third floor.

14:49.789 --> 14:52.890
- That is not the weird part
of that story.

14:54.127 --> 14:55.893
- So what was that earlier?

14:55.962 --> 14:58.329
Why'd you stop me
from dropping the flyers?

14:59.799 --> 15:01.466
- Because I don't like
the Blorphy design.

15:01.534 --> 15:02.967
I'm sorry.
I tried to tell you,

15:03.036 --> 15:05.203
but you were listening
to the dentist music--

15:05.272 --> 15:07.505
- Wait, you didn't like
Blorphy?

15:07.574 --> 15:09.807
I don't like Blorphy either.
He looks like ham.

15:09.876 --> 15:14.379
- Wait, what?
- Yup, just a big ol' ham head.

15:14.447 --> 15:16.614
But I saw how much
you liked it.

15:16.683 --> 15:19.484
And you're, like, the king
of this comic book world, so...

15:19.552 --> 15:21.486
I rolled with it.
- But...

15:21.554 --> 15:22.920
why would you draw him
that way?

15:22.989 --> 15:25.423
- I draw all my characters
with little lunch-meat heads

15:25.492 --> 15:27.959
before I figure out what
they should really look like.

15:28.028 --> 15:30.728
Bologna, salami, ham.

15:30.797 --> 15:34.599
But when you went on and on
about how much you loved it--

15:34.668 --> 15:36.134
- I can't believe this.

15:36.202 --> 15:39.337
[drone whirring]

15:40.740 --> 15:42.840
- Hurley's drone!
- We're saved!

15:42.909 --> 15:45.009
[drone beeping]

15:45.078 --> 15:47.412
Huh?

15:47.480 --> 15:50.682
- What is all this?

15:50.750 --> 15:51.783
[phone rings]

15:51.851 --> 15:55.019
- Go for Hurley.
- Hurley! What is all this?

15:55.088 --> 15:57.822
- It's tea.
You said to find your tea.

15:57.891 --> 16:00.858
- What? No!
I said key, not tea.

16:00.927 --> 16:02.994
Why in the world
would we want tea?

16:03.063 --> 16:04.729
- So that's a hard no
on the teacups

16:04.798 --> 16:06.597
and bear full of honey, then?

16:08.568 --> 16:09.834
- Please put Darby
on the phone.

16:09.903 --> 16:12.303
- Darby.

16:12.372 --> 16:14.605
- Go for Darby.
- Hey, Darby.

16:14.674 --> 16:16.941
It's a long story--
- Wait, don't tell me.

16:18.011 --> 16:19.544
You dropped the key
to the lift,

16:19.612 --> 16:21.312
called Hurley to find it,
but he somehow heard "tea"

16:21.381 --> 16:23.147
and sent his drone up
with tea bags.

16:23.216 --> 16:24.849
- Yes. That.

16:24.918 --> 16:28.052
Listen, I think the key fell
onto a tray of sandwiches.

16:29.556 --> 16:31.823
- The key's in a sandwich!
- Oh!

16:34.361 --> 16:36.627
It's not in this one.

16:38.598 --> 16:40.665
- Have you seen a missing key?
About key size?

16:40.734 --> 16:43.634
Looks sort of, I don't know,
like...a key?

16:45.438 --> 16:46.871
- Darby?

16:46.940 --> 16:48.639
- Where have you been?
- Hey!

16:48.708 --> 16:50.141
- Why weren't you
at the audition the other day?

16:50.210 --> 16:51.509
- Yeah.

16:51.578 --> 16:55.613
♪ We wanted to hear you
siiiiiiing ♪

16:55.682 --> 16:57.181
- Something came up.

16:57.250 --> 16:59.751
Hey, would you all mind looking
in your sandwiches for a key?

16:59.819 --> 17:02.420
- Ooh! Do we win something?

17:02.489 --> 17:05.022
- No.
Just look, Aiden.

17:05.091 --> 17:07.291
[phone rings]

17:07.360 --> 17:09.494
Hello.
- Any luck with that key?

17:09.562 --> 17:10.795
I don't know how much longer
I can be up here.

17:10.864 --> 17:13.598
- Just close your eyes
and take a deep breath.

17:13.666 --> 17:14.899
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

17:14.968 --> 17:16.467
- Says the girl
who was too scared

17:16.536 --> 17:18.469
to sing in front
of her friends.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.705
Sorry.
Was that too brutally honest?

17:20.774 --> 17:24.108
- Yeah, but you're right.

17:24.177 --> 17:25.843
I should take my own advice.

17:28.181 --> 17:30.148
I'm gonna do it.
- Now?

17:30.216 --> 17:31.449
I need you to get us down.

17:31.518 --> 17:32.850
<i> [line beeps]</i>

17:32.919 --> 17:34.652
Hello?

17:34.721 --> 17:36.921
- Hi! Mind if I borrow this
a sec? Thank you.

17:36.990 --> 17:39.924
Excuse me, uh, everyone.

17:39.993 --> 17:42.093
<i> [microphone feedback squeals]</i>
Oh, boy.

17:42.162 --> 17:43.461
That's a lot of eyeballs.

17:44.964 --> 17:46.397
All on me. Uh...

17:46.466 --> 17:50.034
[heartbeat thumping]

17:52.872 --> 17:54.439
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

17:54.507 --> 17:56.207
<i> [whooshing]</i>

17:56.943 --> 17:59.577
Hi, my name is Darby,
and I'm here to audition

17:59.646 --> 18:01.712
to officially join
the musical theater troupe.

18:01.781 --> 18:05.116
- I love it!
The world really is a stage.

18:05.185 --> 18:09.921
- ♪ Whoa ♪

18:09.989 --> 18:13.324
[holding note]

18:13.393 --> 18:14.525
- I just wish you had
told me the truth

18:14.594 --> 18:15.793
about my drawing
from the start.

18:15.862 --> 18:17.295
Then we wouldn't be
in this mess.

18:17.363 --> 18:19.363
- Hey, you weren't exactly
honest with me either.

18:19.432 --> 18:20.898
- That's true.

18:20.967 --> 18:22.800
How about from here on out,
we're just super honest

18:22.869 --> 18:24.969
with each other about anything
and everything?

18:25.038 --> 18:27.738
- Deal. Starting now.
- Starting now.

18:27.807 --> 18:29.440
I don't love that you wear
so much red.

18:29.509 --> 18:31.409
Blue is obviously your color.
- Wow.

18:31.478 --> 18:33.845
Okay, so we're starting
right now.

18:33.913 --> 18:35.580
Well, I don't love how you
always try to talk to me

18:35.648 --> 18:37.415
when I'm eating.
- And I don't love

18:37.484 --> 18:38.649
that you're such a quiet eater.

18:38.718 --> 18:40.518
I can never tell
if you're eating or not.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.988
[laughter]

18:44.057 --> 18:46.290
- I'm sorry I wasn't honest
with you in the first place.

18:46.359 --> 18:47.425
- It's okay.

18:47.494 --> 18:49.427
And if I'm being
brutally honest...

18:49.496 --> 18:50.628
I really love your writing,

18:50.697 --> 18:52.463
and I feel lucky
I get to draw for you.

18:53.600 --> 18:56.133
- Well, if I'm being
brutally honest...

18:57.370 --> 18:59.136
You're an amazing artist,
and I can't wait to see

18:59.205 --> 19:01.839
what we accomplish together.

19:01.908 --> 19:03.441
Hopefully the first thing
we accomplish together

19:03.510 --> 19:05.109
is getting back down
on the ground.

19:07.614 --> 19:10.848
- [holding note]

19:10.917 --> 19:13.317
♪ ♪

19:13.386 --> 19:16.454
[cheers and applause]

19:18.591 --> 19:21.292
- Brava!

19:21.361 --> 19:22.460
- Welcome to the troupe!

19:22.529 --> 19:25.096
- Great job!
- Congrats!

19:25.164 --> 19:26.898
- Darby, the key!

19:28.201 --> 19:30.001
I found one in a sandwich.

19:30.069 --> 19:31.802
You think this is the one
they were looking for?

19:36.576 --> 19:39.343
[drone whirring]

19:39.412 --> 19:40.645
- There it is!

19:40.713 --> 19:42.213
[drone whirring]

19:42.282 --> 19:45.416
It's back!
And it's got the key this time!

19:45.485 --> 19:47.685
- Oh. Finally!

19:47.754 --> 19:49.387
Let's get off this thing.

19:49.455 --> 19:51.255
Man, that could have been
a disaster.

19:51.324 --> 19:53.190
- Yeah, thank goodness
we came clean to each other

19:53.259 --> 19:54.959
before anyone saw those.

19:55.028 --> 19:56.160
- People would've seen
that giant ham,

19:56.229 --> 19:57.828
and our graphic novel
would be toast.

19:57.897 --> 19:59.263
- Stop talking
about ham and toast.

19:59.332 --> 20:01.933
I'm starving.
When we get down, I'm--

20:02.001 --> 20:03.334
[drone grinding]

20:03.403 --> 20:04.936
- Look out!
- Grab him!

20:05.004 --> 20:07.738
- Don't worry, I got you!
- Oh, no! I'm slipping!

20:07.807 --> 20:10.541
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

20:12.545 --> 20:15.179
- No, I don't!
I don't got you!

20:15.248 --> 20:18.349
- Whoa!

20:18.418 --> 20:21.953
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

20:22.989 --> 20:25.189
- Finished the new design
for Blorphy.

20:25.258 --> 20:27.692
What do you think?

20:27.760 --> 20:29.694
- I think he looks
like a cauliflower.

20:29.762 --> 20:32.063
- Ha! That was a test.
You passed.

20:32.131 --> 20:34.732
Here is the real design.

20:34.801 --> 20:36.867
- Ruby, I love it!
It's perfect!

20:37.937 --> 20:40.972
both: Aww, I love him.

20:41.040 --> 20:44.408
- Too bad everyone saw that
horrible ham drawing first.

20:44.477 --> 20:45.743
Ugh.
- It actually worked out.

20:45.812 --> 20:46.978
Since Blorphy looked like ham

20:47.046 --> 20:48.946
and the hashtag said
NextGreatHero,

20:49.015 --> 20:51.015
everyone just thought it was
a promotion for Super Sammies.

20:51.084 --> 20:53.884
- Yeah. In fact,
the owner liked it so much

20:53.953 --> 20:57.221
that he paid us to use Blorphy
for his restaurant's mascot.

20:57.290 --> 20:58.889
They're renaming him Hammy.

20:58.958 --> 21:01.626
- Sweet.
How much is he paying you?

21:01.694 --> 21:04.261
- A lifetime supply
of sandwiches.

21:06.566 --> 21:09.000
all: Gah!

21:09.068 --> 21:12.103
Sorry, Hammy.
You scared us.

21:12.171 --> 21:15.406
I ordered a dozen Guardians
of the Grilled Cheeses.

21:15.475 --> 21:16.607
Dig in!

21:20.546 --> 21:21.746
- Mmm.

21:23.316 --> 21:25.916
Really? That's the loudest
you can chew?

21:25.985 --> 21:27.718
- This is how I chew.
I'm a soft chewer.

21:27.787 --> 21:31.088
- Here. Up, down. Up, down.
Up, down. Up--

21:31.157 --> 21:33.024
- Ow! I think I chipped
a tooth.

21:33.092 --> 21:35.393
- Ooh! I'll call Dr. Abrams.

21:37.630 --> 21:39.664
No, it's not an emergency.

21:39.732 --> 21:41.999
Yes, I'll hold.

21:42.068 --> 21:45.136
<i> [cheery music playing]</i>

21:45.204 --> 21:52.109
<i> ♪ ♪</i>
